         <abstract>
            <p>A method for computing $\int^x_0 f(t) dt, x = (0, 1)$ is outlined, where $f(t)$ may have singularities at $t = 0$ and $t = 1$. The method depends on the approximation properties of Whittaker cardinal, or sinc function expansions; the general technique may be used for semi-infinite or infinite intervals in addition to (0, 1). Tables of numerical results are given.</p>
          </abstract>
